                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5034 China—Searchlight Publishing Co./30:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1"
                            type="to">Cunningham</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-08T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 8, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>236. Your 361, August 4, 1 p.m., paragraph 3, first sentence stating that
                    “Searchlight Publishing Company have never been registered in the Consulate
                    General”.</p>
                <p>Your despatch No. 8090 of January 22 to Department<note n="21" xml:id="d734fn21"
                        >Not printed.</note> transmits for Department’s consideration copy of an
                    application made by <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName> for
                    registration of the Searchlight Publishing Company. Department’s instruction in
                    reply to March 28<note n="21" xml:id="d734fn22">Not printed.</note> stated that
                    the Department “does not desire to raise any objection to the approval by you of
                    the application for registration”. Please inform Department what transpired
                    thereafter in connection with the application.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
